spec: as3391
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(asyncio)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/asyncio.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 673 (as3391): __int__, __float__, __complex__ dict-presence checks for asyncio types."
    - "Theme: __int__/__float__/__complex__ dict-presence (int(x), float(x), complex(x))."
    - "All values False — asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives with no numeric conversion support."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: asyncio.Task, asyncio.Future, asyncio.Event, asyncio.Lock, asyncio.Semaphore, asyncio.BoundedSemaphore, asyncio.Condition, asyncio.Queue, asyncio.PriorityQueue, asyncio.LifoQueue."
    - "Key finding (__int__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __int__. int() delegates to __int__ (numbers.Integral protocol) when defined. asyncio types implement no numeric data model of any kind — confirmed false across waves 658–672 for all arithmetic, bitwise, reflected arithmetic, reflected bitwise, in-place augmented assignment, unary numeric, rounding, and integer-index operators. int(task), int(future), int(event), int(lock), int(semaphore), int(queue) are not valid Python expressions. asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives with no integer magnitude to convert."
    - "Key finding (__float__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __float__. float() delegates to __float__ (numbers.Real protocol) when defined. asyncio types define no numeric protocol — there is no real-valued magnitude associated with any asyncio concurrency primitive. float(event), float(task), float(queue) are not meaningful Python expressions. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore encapsulate a permit counter fully behind acquire()/release() coroutines; the counter is not exposed for numeric float conversion. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are item stores whose qsize() returns an integer, but qsize() is a method — not the object's float value — and __float__ is not defined on any Queue subclass."
    - "Key finding (__complex__): all 10 asyncio classes return false for __complex__. complex() delegates to __complex__ (numbers.Complex protocol) when defined. asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives — none of them represent a complex number. asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition are boolean-state guards; even though Event.is_set() returns bool, asyncio.Event itself does not define __complex__. asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore encapsulate a counter but the counter is not convertible to complex via __complex__. asyncio.Task/Future are pending coroutine result handles; __complex__ is not defined. asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue are item stores; complex(queue) is not a valid Python expression."
    - "Continues the all-false run from wave 656 (__call__/__len__/__getitem__) through wave 673 (__int__/__float__/__complex__) — eighteen consecutive waves of 100% false results for asyncio types."
    - "Cross-wave summary for asyncio subjects:"
    - "  Wave 656 (as3136): __call__/__len__/__getitem__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 657 (as3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 658 (as3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 659 (as3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 14."
    - "  Wave 660 (as3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 661 (as3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 662 (as3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 663 (as3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 664 (as3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 665 (as3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 666 (as3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 667 (as3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 668 (as3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 669 (as3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 670 (as3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 671 (as3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 672 (as3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 10."
    - "  Wave 673 (as3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 10."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __int__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__int__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __int__.
# int() delegates to __int__ (numbers.Integral protocol) when defined.
# asyncio types implement no numeric data model of any kind.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state synchronization guards with no
#   integer magnitude to convert; int(event) is not a valid Python expression.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: permit-counter objects whose internal
#   integer state is fully encapsulated behind acquire()/release() coroutines.
#   The counter is not exposed through __int__ or any numeric data model method.
# asyncio.Task/Future: pending coroutine result handles; int(task) and
#   int(future) are not valid Python expressions.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: ordered item stores with no numeric
#   data model; int(queue) is not defined.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

