# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __complex__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__complex__')
#
# All 10 asyncio classes return false for __complex__.
# complex() delegates to __complex__ (numbers.Complex protocol) when defined.
# asyncio types are coroutine-based concurrency primitives — none of them
#   represent a complex number. No real or imaginary component is associated
#   with any asyncio synchronization or communication primitive.
# asyncio.Event/Lock/Condition: boolean-state guards; even though Event.is_set()
#   returns bool and bool is a numeric subtype, asyncio.Event itself does not
#   define __complex__ — the guard object is not a complex number.
# asyncio.Semaphore/BoundedSemaphore: encapsulate a counter but the counter
#   is not convertible to complex via __complex__.
# asyncio.Task/Future: coroutine result handles; complex(task) and
#   complex(future) are not valid Python expressions.
# asyncio.Queue/PriorityQueue/LifoQueue: item stores; complex(queue) is not
#   defined. The queue object cannot be used as a complex number.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

